"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#social","cachedResultName":"#social"},"text":"=✅ Generate blog drafts with Airtable and WordPress automatically — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[4428,400],"id":"ae53a871-efab-42db-98aa-74b0072c912e","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"f3d58f08-3bac-4a12-b662-5d8b00711248","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"683aa841-e590-4cb5-8bb1-86ca23867d61","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"19e6149f-d6e0-46d7-9285-94484fa85ee9","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[3780,1420],"id":"55bad642-0201-4eff-b9c5-a78176732c24","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#social","cachedResultName":"#social"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[4104,1420],"id":"93b7165e-db6f-4d78-8178-e79937c3fb95","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hourly Schedule\n\nStarts the workflow on a timer — every 1 h. No input data; downstream nodes fetch what they need.\n\nNext: Required Fields Present?","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"0053b76d-9d43-1edf-c12b-9a1908ea0658","name":"Note: Hourly Schedule"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Required Fields Present?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.content }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Build the Brief · ②→ Abort — Malformed Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"01660d99-cab5-0013-49c0-9ad4d3a3e370","name":"Note: Required Fields Present?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Abort — Malformed Input\n\nFails fast with a clear message; triggers the error workflow instead of processing bad data.","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,1030],"id":"c8a23291-76e1-d962-abdb-3c5817778679","name":"Note: Abort — Malformed Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Build the Brief\n\nShapes the item: writes `brief`, `tone`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Draft with AI Writer","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"c00b845c-cb0c-2a2b-a875-983d9250ce99","name":"Note: Build the Brief"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Draft with AI Writer\n\nSingle fixed LLM step (no tool choice) — cheaper and more predictable than an agent.\n\nPorts: ①→ Refine with AI Editor · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"3826744f-1a94-1f10-bc58-93721b79cc67","name":"Note: Draft with AI Writer"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Groq Writer Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `llama-3.3-70b-versatile`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Draft with AI Writer** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 Groq API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,1090],"id":"5f50e67e-7606-0ec2-58ef-f4d9eba7ef62","name":"Note: Groq Writer Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Refine with AI Editor\n\nSingle fixed LLM step (no tool choice) — cheaper and more predictable than an agent.\n\nPorts: ①→ Publish Draft to WordPress · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,520],"id":"a82c1fb8-3d68-89e9-f664-2063e861c5aa","name":"Note: Refine with AI Editor"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Groq Editor Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `llama-3.3-70b-versatile`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Refine with AI Editor** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 Groq API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1452,1090],"id":"2e86b595-f543-4db4-09f3-ad8517f64ef3","name":"Note: Groq Editor Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Publish Draft to WordPress\n\nwordpress — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Guard Non-Empty content · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 WordPress credentials","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1776,520],"id":"ca825830-c521-76d4-622a-ff3e9f1a6c80","name":"Note: Publish Draft to WordPress"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty content\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2100,520],"id":"ff943172-3128-f6f4-01f7-59b1b06939ec","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty content"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2424,520],"id":"9ec9bf96-2664-ebfe-6e24-40bd3187c3ba","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2748,520],"id":"1c6b7572-e23a-5807-d57b-14bc87f81082","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Sort Posts Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3072,520],"id":"7f8323a0-bbc1-da93-6ba6-ffbe7fbe1e18","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Posts Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3396,520],"id":"3498a2a5-560a-043d-d969-12e7ee581e8b","name":"Note: Sort Posts Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Airtable)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3720,520],"id":"51072dff-319b-37f4-0c3a-bbff3659940d","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Airtable)\n\nairtable — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4044,520],"id":"0111f424-a1f9-654b-d3c8-b0a657cc08d9","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Airtable)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4368,520],"id":"748f3420-bdb6-5c3c-8e79-010154fc57d7","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3720,1540],"id":"5689318e-295a-4a37-9277-fcdc2534a790","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4044,1540],"id":"863f96a5-57a2-23fc-623a-b6dbbc22b533","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Generate blog drafts with Airtable and WordPress automatically\n\n**Pattern:** Content Generation · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nGenerate blog drafts with Airtable and WordPress automatically. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual scheduling is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Required Fields Present? → Build the Brief → Draft with AI Writer → Refine with AI Editor → Publish Draft to WordPress → Guard Non-Empty content → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to content generation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating scheduling in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Airtable PAT; Groq API key; Slack OAuth2; WordPress credentials.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"16259cf0-85c2-4529-9990-58ffa9a130c9","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-20],"id":"8062b538-2a55-9a51-5f63-1ffb06b33315","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-20],"id":"4eb4ee67-6a26-cc5a-46bf-18de596169cb","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your scheduling process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-20],"id":"2feaaf5d-1dd0-2956-185d-c45cea759220","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Hourly Schedule":{"main":[[{"node":"Required Fields Present?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Required Fields Present?":{"main":[[{"node":"Build the Brief","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Abort — Malformed Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Build the Brief":{"main":[[{"node":"Draft with AI Writer","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Groq Writer Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Draft with AI Writer","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Draft with AI Writer":{"main":[[{"node":"Refine with AI Editor","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Groq Editor Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Refine with AI Editor","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Refine with AI Editor":{"main":[[{"node":"Publish Draft to WordPress","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Publish Draft to WordPress":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty content","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty content":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Posts Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Posts Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Airtable)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Airtable)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"785826ca-0da6-4b1f-aa42-023bd461eb19","id":"FDX07048"}